{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01To9LJJmUAGnyRoPX6qmMGZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture:\n\n1. There's a `crdb-cluster-public` ClusterIP service in the `cockroachdb` namespace exposing ports 26257 (SQL) and 8080 (DB Console/HTTP).\n2. No configmaps in ingress-nginx yet.\n3. No ingress resources yet.\n\nI need to:\n1. Create an Ingress resource for HTTPS access to the DB Console at `crdb-ui.example.com` (port 8080)\n2. Configure TCP passthrough for SQL traffic on port 26257 via ingress-nginx\n\nFor the HTTPS DB Console:\nCockroachDB's console already runs over HTTPS internally, so I can either use TLS passthrough with the nginx annotation or terminate TLS at the ingress layer with a certificate. Since the requirement specifies TLS is needed and CockroachDB manages its own certificates, I'll use TLS passthrough to avoid certificate conflicts. I need to figure out whether the CockroachDB cluster is running in secure mode with certificates or insecure mode, since that determines whether port 8080 is HTTP or HTTPS and affects how I configure the ingress.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":285,"cache_read_input_tokens":29497,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":285},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d22d7a90-9dbc-4216-9a4d-445a19c94a36","uuid":"fa94b1e6-1875-48ac-9fdc-4853844e5394","request_id":"req_011Cc5FanoapA5WyCEjgMxNf"}
