{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YLtXCBZs9KTcDybxiZwGpM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Everything looks good! Let me now verify the setup end-to-end:\n\n1. The ingress-nginx controller is running\n2. The service exposes ports 80, 443, and 26257 (mapped to NodePort)\n3. The Ingress resource is created with TLS for `crdb-ui.example.com`\n4. The tcp-services ConfigMap has `26257` pointing to `cockroachdb/crdb-cluster-public:26257`\n\nLet me do a quick functional test:\n1. Test HTTPS access to the DB Console\n2. Test SQL access on port 26257\n\nFor testing, I need to know the IP of the ingress-nginx controller service. \n\nSince this is a kind cluster, the LoadBalancer will be pending, so I'll need to use the node IP and the NodePort values for both port 443 and 26257.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":444,"cache_read_input_tokens":39172,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":444},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d22d7a90-9dbc-4216-9a4d-445a19c94a36","uuid":"8db93873-6aac-49f2-a76b-af0bb6c6c3ea","request_id":"req_011Cc5FoWr14Gd2MYqauCcLH"}
